1
00:05:56,055 --> 00:05:58,545
Hey, Stevie, you okay?

2
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:02,508
I got...

3
00:06:06,772 --> 00:06:09,227
I got the wind knocked out of me.

4
00:06:09,315 --> 00:06:11,106
Looks like a cave.

5
00:06:21,659 --> 00:06:24,363
Stevie, what's goin' on?

6
00:06:29,206 --> 00:06:31,079
It's a human skull!

7
00:06:31,166 --> 00:06:34,450
- Toss it up here!
- No way! It's mine.

8
00:06:34,544 --> 00:06:38,161
Anyway, there's bones
all over the place, man!

9
00:06:52,392 --> 00:06:53,933
What the...

10
00:07:16,786 --> 00:07:18,861
Stevie?

11
00:07:18,955 --> 00:07:21,196
- Hey, Stevie!
- You okay?

12
00:07:24,626 --> 00:07:27,994
Hey, man... let's get outta here!

13
00:08:09,454 --> 00:08:11,529
Give me a 14-footer!

14
00:08:13,416 --> 00:08:17,709
This is Captain Miles Cooles.
Rescue situation in progress.

15
00:08:17,794 --> 00:08:22,205
Rope's in the hole.
Let's go. Two down.

16
00:08:29,053 --> 00:08:31,128
What ya got, TC? Talk to me.

17
00:08:33,432 --> 00:08:35,424
Do you see the boy?

18
00:08:39,145 --> 00:08:42,394
Come back, TC. You see the kid?

19
00:08:44,191 --> 00:08:46,064
Danny, check TC's radio.

20
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,604
TC?

21
00:08:48,694 --> 00:08:50,769
Glenn, Sal, in the hole!

22
00:09:22,305 --> 00:09:26,052
- Get those people outta here!
- Move 'em back!

23
00:09:26,141 --> 00:09:27,718
Move back, folks!

24
00:09:29,227 --> 00:09:35,228
I sent four men down there for the boy.
Report is, his eyes had turned black.

25
00:09:35,315 --> 00:09:38,730
Now we've lost communication with my men.

26
00:09:53,872 --> 00:09:55,828
What about my men?

27
00:09:59,877 --> 00:10:02,449
What about my men!

28
00:10:15,473 --> 00:10:17,880
What the hell is this?

29
00:10:46,665 --> 00:10:48,372
It's Bronschweig.

30
00:10:48,458 --> 00:10:53,332
Sir, the impossible scenario
that we never planned for?

31
00:10:53,712 --> 00:10:56,249
We'd better come up with a plan.

32
00:11:29,032 --> 00:11:31,736
We've evacuated the building.

33
00:11:31,826 --> 00:11:37,411
- There's no trace of an explosive device.
- You sent the dogs through?

34
00:11:37,497 --> 00:11:38,410
Yes, sir.

35
00:11:38,498 --> 00:11:40,324
Send 'em through again.

36
00:11:44,003 --> 00:11:45,461
All right, guys.

37
00:11:45,546 --> 00:11:47,621
Let's do it again!

38
00:12:14,903 --> 00:12:16,776
Mulder, it's me.

39
00:12:16,863 --> 00:12:19,270
- Where are you, Scully?
- On the roof.

40
00:12:19,406 --> 00:12:22,192
- Findanyhing?
- No, I haven't.

41
00:12:22,993 --> 00:12:24,273
What's wrong?

42
00:12:24,369 --> 00:12:28,068
I just climbed up 12 floors,
I'm hot, I'm thirsty...

43
00:12:28,163 --> 00:12:31,033
...and I'm wondering what I'm doing.

44
00:12:31,124 --> 00:12:32,997
You're looking fora bomb.

45
00:12:33,084 --> 00:12:36,499
But the threat was made
on the Federal Building.

46
00:12:36,587 --> 00:12:38,662
They have that covered.

47
00:12:38,755 --> 00:12:45,503
When a bomb threat is called in, the rational
purpose of it is to allow us to find the bomb.

48
00:12:45,594 --> 00:12:50,053
The rational object of terrorism
is to promote terror.

49
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:56,888
There's a model behavioural pattern for every
case where a threat has turned up a bomb.

50
00:12:57,187 --> 00:13:00,769
And ifwe ignore that data, as we have done...

51
00:13:00,857 --> 00:13:05,648
...the chances are great that,
if there is a bomb, we might not find it.

52
00:13:05,736 --> 00:13:07,811
Lives could be lost.

53
00:13:07,987 --> 00:13:08,852
Mulder?

54
00:13:10,198 --> 00:13:11,478
Mulder?

55
00:13:11,574 --> 00:13:12,355
Boom!

56
00:13:12,449 --> 00:13:13,859
Jesus, Mulder!

57
00:13:13,951 --> 00:13:16,406
Whatever happened to hunches?

58
00:13:17,704 --> 00:13:20,704
Random acts of unpredictability.

59
00:13:20,789 --> 00:13:26,458
If we fail to anticipate the unforeseen
in a universe of infinite possibilities...

60
00:13:26,544 --> 00:13:32,296
...we may find ourselves at the mercy
of anything that cannot be categorised.

61
00:13:34,926 --> 00:13:38,922
What are we doin' up here, Scully?
It's hotter than hell.

62
00:13:42,932 --> 00:13:48,470
I know you're bored, but unconventional
thinking will only get you into trouble now.

63
00:13:48,562 --> 00:13:53,223
- Why do you think I'm bored?
- Quit looking for what isn't there.

64
00:13:53,316 --> 00:13:56,648
They've closed the X-Files.
We follow procedure now.

65
00:13:56,735 --> 00:14:02,569
Let's make a bomb threat to Houston.
It's free-beer night at the Astrodome.

66
00:14:07,369 --> 00:14:08,317
Now what?

67
00:14:08,411 --> 00:14:10,070
It's locked?

68
00:14:10,163 --> 00:14:13,246
So much for anticipating the unforeseen!

69
00:14:16,209 --> 00:14:18,616
- I had you.
- No, you didn't.

70
00:14:18,711 --> 00:14:21,166
- I had you big time.
- You had nothing.

71
00:14:21,255 --> 00:14:22,879
I saw you jiggle the handle.

72
00:14:24,966 --> 00:14:28,630
I saw your face.
There was a definite moment of panic.

73
00:14:28,719 --> 00:14:32,846
You've never seen me panic.
When I panic, I make this face.

74
00:14:32,931 --> 00:14:34,045
That was it.

75
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:38,302
- You didn't see that face.
- I saw that face. You're buying.

76
00:14:40,395 --> 00:14:42,434
Coke? Pepsi? Saline IV?

77
00:14:42,522 --> 00:14:44,597
Somethin' sweet.

78
00:16:03,546 --> 00:16:06,416
Scully.

79
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:08,166
I've found the bomb.

80
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:11,460
You're funny. Where are you, Mulder?

81
00:16:11,803 --> 00:16:13,878
I'm in the vending room.

82
00:16:15,472 --> 00:16:18,388
Is that you pounding?

83
00:16:18,475 --> 00:16:21,677
Yeah. Get somebody to open that door.

84
00:16:22,478 --> 00:16:25,928
- Nice try, Mulder.
- It's in the soda machine.

85
00:16:26,023 --> 00:16:28,394
You got 14 minutes to evacuate.

86
00:16:30,109 --> 00:16:31,935
Come on, Mulder.

87
00:16:32,027 --> 00:16:33,437
13.56...

88
00:16:33,529 --> 00:16:35,604
13.54...

89
00:16:36,156 --> 00:16:38,195
13.52...

90
00:16:38,283 --> 00:16:39,527
13.50...

91
00:16:39,617 --> 00:16:43,779
You see a pattern emerging here, Scully?

92
00:16:50,918 --> 00:16:52,826
I'll get you outta there!

93
00:16:58,215 --> 00:17:01,334
I need this building evacuated in ten minutes!

94
00:17:01,426 --> 00:17:05,837
Have the fire department block off
a one-mile radius around the building!

95
00:17:05,930 --> 00:17:09,512
- Ten minutes?
- Don't think! Just make it happen!

96
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,093
This is Security...

97
00:17:13,478 --> 00:17:17,724
This is Special Agent Dana Scully.
I need to speak with SAC Michaud.

98
00:17:17,815 --> 00:17:19,854
He's got the wrong building.

99
00:17:35,787 --> 00:17:38,573
- Where is it?
- Vending machine.

100
00:17:38,665 --> 00:17:40,621
He's locked in with it.

101
00:18:02,142 --> 00:18:05,973
You know that face I just showed you?
I'm making it again.

102
00:18:06,479 --> 00:18:10,262
Move awayfrom the door.
We're coming through.

103
00:18:23,243 --> 00:18:24,405
Clear!

104
00:18:30,749 --> 00:18:34,995
Tell me that's just soda pop
in those canisters.

105
00:18:40,923 --> 00:18:43,923
It's just what it looks like. A big IED.

106
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:47,676
Ten gallons of Astrolite.

107
00:18:48,721 --> 00:18:52,883
Okay. Get everybody outta here.
Clear the area.

108
00:18:54,434 --> 00:18:59,141
- Someone's gotta stay here with you.
- I gave you an order to evacuate.

109
00:18:59,230 --> 00:19:01,387
Can you defuse it?

110
00:19:02,107 --> 00:19:03,648
Yes, I can.

111
00:19:03,734 --> 00:19:07,896
- We got four minutes to find out.
- Did you hear what I said?

112
00:19:07,987 --> 00:19:10,311
Get out!

113
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:15,824
Come on, Mulder.

114
00:19:58,987 --> 00:20:00,979
Mulder, what are you doing!

115
00:20:01,072 --> 00:20:03,776
- Something's wrong!
- Mulder!

116
00:20:04,199 --> 00:20:08,030
- Something's not right.
- Get in the car! There's no time!

117
00:20:09,287 --> 00:20:10,567
Let's go!

118
00:20:21,338 --> 00:20:23,413
Come on, come on!

119
00:21:28,643 --> 00:21:31,596
Next time, you're buying.

120
00:21:45,323 --> 00:21:48,607
In light of Waco and Ruby Ridge...

121
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:53,407
...there is a need at the Attorney General's
office to place responsibility...

122
00:21:53,496 --> 00:21:59,533
...for the catastrophic destruction of public
property and loss of life due to terrorism.

123
00:21:59,626 --> 00:22:04,251
Details are unclear, but we're under
pressure from the Attorney General...

124
00:22:04,338 --> 00:22:08,915
...to give a true account of what happened,
so she can issue a public statement.

125
00:22:09,009 --> 00:22:13,586
We know now that five people
died in the explosion:

126
00:22:13,721 --> 00:22:14,883
Special...

127
00:22:18,641 --> 00:22:23,634
Special Agent in Charge Darius Michaud
who was trying to defuse the bomb...

128
00:22:23,729 --> 00:22:26,397
...three firemen from Dallas, and a young boy.

129
00:22:27,941 --> 00:22:32,732
Excuse me? The firemen and the young boy
were found in the building?

130
00:22:32,819 --> 00:22:38,322
Agent Mulder, since you weren't on time
for this hearing, please step outside...

131
00:22:38,407 --> 00:22:43,151
...so that we can hear
Agent Scully's version of the facts.

132
00:22:43,245 --> 00:22:49,745
- We were told the building was clear.
- You'll get your turn. Please step outside.

133
00:23:09,766 --> 00:23:13,098
They're still talking to Agent Scully.

134
00:23:13,394 --> 00:23:14,935
About what?

135
00:23:15,020 --> 00:23:19,266
They want to know why
she was in the wrong building.

136
00:23:19,399 --> 00:23:21,474
She was with me.

137
00:23:24,361 --> 00:23:29,983
You don't get it, do you? There's $45 million
worth of damage to the city of Dallas.

138
00:23:30,074 --> 00:23:33,109
Lives have been lost.
No suspects have been named.

139
00:23:33,202 --> 00:23:36,784
The story is that
this could've been prevented.

140
00:23:36,871 --> 00:23:38,993
They wanna blame us?

141
00:23:41,083 --> 00:23:45,411
We both know that if it looks bad,
it's bad for the FBI.

142
00:23:45,503 --> 00:23:48,171
Blame has to be assigned somewhere.

143
00:23:49,381 --> 00:23:55,299
- But Agent Scully doesn't deserve this.
- She's saying the same about you.

144
00:23:55,386 --> 00:24:01,387
I breached protocol. I broke contact with
the SAC. I left him alone with the device.

145
00:24:01,475 --> 00:24:04,594
Agent Scully says you wanted to go back.

146
00:24:04,685 --> 00:24:05,929
No.

147
00:24:13,734 --> 00:24:16,224
They're asking for you, sir.

148
00:24:17,404 --> 00:24:18,897
Thank you.

149
00:24:22,492 --> 00:24:27,199
- You don't have to protect me.
- I told them the truth.

150
00:24:27,287 --> 00:24:29,742
They're trying to divide us.

151
00:24:30,832 --> 00:24:34,200
They have divided us. They're splitting us up.

152
00:24:34,293 --> 00:24:36,664
What are you talking about?

153
00:24:36,753 --> 00:24:40,452
I meet with OPR in two days
for reassignment.

154
00:24:40,548 --> 00:24:41,958
They put us together!

155
00:24:42,049 --> 00:24:46,377
So I could invalidate your investigations
into the paranormal. But...

156
00:24:46,469 --> 00:24:48,793
...I think this goes deeper than that now.

157
00:24:48,888 --> 00:24:53,050
- They're doing this to me.
- They're not doing this.

158
00:24:56,728 --> 00:25:02,765
I left behind a career in medicine because
I thought I could make a difference at the FBI.

159
00:25:02,858 --> 00:25:05,692
But it hasn't turned out that way.

160
00:25:05,777 --> 00:25:11,611
And now ifthey transfer me to Omaha
or Cleveland or some field office...

161
00:25:11,698 --> 00:25:18,826
...it doesn't hold the interest for me that it
once did. Not after what I've seen and done.

162
00:25:20,914 --> 00:25:22,705
You're quitting.

163
00:25:24,875 --> 00:25:28,954
Maybe you should ask yourself
if your heart's still in it, too.

164
00:25:33,799 --> 00:25:36,633
Agent Mulder, you're up.

165
00:25:36,718 --> 00:25:38,793
I'm sorry.

166
00:25:41,722 --> 00:25:42,800
Mulder...

167
00:25:46,935 --> 00:25:48,678
Good luck.

168
00:26:10,954 --> 00:26:16,742
I'd say this about exceeds
your minimum daily requirement.

169
00:26:19,378 --> 00:26:24,252
Whoa! You've gotta train
for that kind of heavy lifting.

170
00:26:25,258 --> 00:26:27,333
Poopy day?

171
00:26:32,555 --> 00:26:33,965
So...

172
00:26:34,056 --> 00:26:35,847
...what do you do?

173
00:26:37,017 --> 00:26:38,890
- What do I do?
- Mm-hm.

174
00:26:42,438 --> 00:26:49,055
I'm the key figure in a government plot
to deny the existence of extraterrestrials.

175
00:26:49,152 --> 00:26:54,441
It's a global conspiracy with key players
in the highest levels of power.

176
00:26:54,531 --> 00:26:59,322
And it reaches down into the lives of every
man, woman and child on this planet.

177
00:27:01,245 --> 00:27:04,245
So, of course, no-one believes me.

178
00:27:04,331 --> 00:27:08,742
I'm an annoyance to my superiors,
a joke to my peers. They call me Spooky.

179
00:27:08,918 --> 00:27:12,202
Spooky Mulder,
whose sister was abducted by aliens...

180
00:27:12,296 --> 00:27:15,913
...who chases after little green men
with a badge and a gun...

181
00:27:16,007 --> 00:27:19,209
...shouting to the heavens
to anyone who will listen...

182
00:27:19,301 --> 00:27:21,458
...that the sky is falling.

183
00:27:21,553 --> 00:27:26,095
And when it hits,
it's gonna be the shitstorm of all time.

184
00:27:29,351 --> 00:27:30,809
Well...

185
00:27:32,437 --> 00:27:36,220
- I would say that about does it, Spooky.
- Does what?

186
00:27:36,315 --> 00:27:39,185
Looks like 86 is your lucky number.

187
00:27:48,700 --> 00:27:52,364
You know, one is the Ioneliest number.

188
00:28:26,022 --> 00:28:26,970
Hello?

189
00:28:27,064 --> 00:28:29,139
- Whoa!
- Sorry.

190
00:28:47,664 --> 00:28:49,572
That official FBI business?

191
00:28:50,875 --> 00:28:52,037
What?

192
00:28:52,126 --> 00:28:55,660
Bet the Bureau's accusing you
of the same thing in Dallas.

193
00:28:55,754 --> 00:29:00,213
Standing around holding your yank
while bombs are exploding.

194
00:29:04,428 --> 00:29:06,420
Do I know you?

195
00:29:06,513 --> 00:29:10,047
No, but I've been watching your career
for a good while.

196
00:29:10,141 --> 00:29:14,007
Back when you were
a promising young agent. Before that.

197
00:29:15,270 --> 00:29:18,353
- You come out here for a reason?
- Yeah...

198
00:29:18,439 --> 00:29:20,514
I did.

199
00:29:21,984 --> 00:29:24,225
My name is Kurtzweil.

200
00:29:24,319 --> 00:29:26,441
Dr Alvin Kurtzweil.

201
00:29:26,529 --> 00:29:30,988
- Am I supposed to know that name?
- Old friend of your father's.

202
00:29:31,617 --> 00:29:34,985
At the State Department
we were fellow travellers.

203
00:29:35,078 --> 00:29:39,157
But his disenchantment outlasted mine.

204
00:29:48,714 --> 00:29:50,789
How'd you find me?

205
00:29:51,424 --> 00:29:55,420
I heard you come in here.
I figured you'd need a drink tonight.

206
00:29:55,511 --> 00:30:00,218
- You a reporter?
- A doctor, which I mentioned. OB-GYN.

207
00:30:00,307 --> 00:30:02,714
You got something to tell me, say it.

208
00:30:02,809 --> 00:30:06,259
There's something you don't know
about the bombing in Dallas.

209
00:30:06,353 --> 00:30:07,633
What's that?

210
00:30:07,729 --> 00:30:11,975
SAC Darius Michaud never tried
or intended to defuse that bomb.

211
00:30:12,066 --> 00:30:14,852
He just let it explode in his face, huh?

212
00:30:14,943 --> 00:30:19,070
What is no-one asking? Why that building?
Why not the Federal Building?

213
00:30:19,155 --> 00:30:21,360
It was too well guarded.

214
00:30:21,449 --> 00:30:23,939
They bombed the other building...

215
00:30:24,034 --> 00:30:27,069
...because it did have Federal officers there.

216
00:30:27,162 --> 00:30:29,913
The Federal Emergency
Management Agency...

217
00:30:29,997 --> 00:30:33,447
...had a quarantine office there,
where the bodies were found.

218
00:30:33,542 --> 00:30:37,538
That's the thing you didn't know.
The thing you'd never think to check.

219
00:30:37,628 --> 00:30:40,200
Those people were already dead.

220
00:30:42,132 --> 00:30:44,207
Before the bomb went off?

221
00:30:44,301 --> 00:30:46,127
That's what I'm saying.

222
00:30:48,554 --> 00:30:50,842
Darius Michaud was a 22-year veteran...

223
00:30:50,931 --> 00:30:55,805
Michaud was a patriot. The people he was
loyal to know their way around Dallas.

224
00:30:55,893 --> 00:31:00,435
They blew that building to hide something.
Something they couldn't predict.

225
00:31:00,522 --> 00:31:04,435
They blew up a building
just to hide the bodies of those firemen?

226
00:31:04,525 --> 00:31:06,481
And one little boy.

227
00:31:07,736 --> 00:31:09,811
I think you're full of shit.

228
00:31:10,989 --> 00:31:13,146
Do you?

229
00:31:17,661 --> 00:31:20,281
Arlington, please.

230
00:31:34,550 --> 00:31:37,384
Actually, no, let's go to Georgetown.

231
00:31:38,553 --> 00:31:41,043
Let's go to Georgetown.

232
00:32:08,994 --> 00:32:11,780
- I woke you. Did I wake you?
- No.

233
00:32:11,871 --> 00:32:13,744
Why not? It's 3am.

234
00:32:13,831 --> 00:32:15,906
Are you drunk?

235
00:32:17,084 --> 00:32:20,203
L-I was until about 20 minutes ago, yeah.

236
00:32:20,295 --> 00:32:23,745
Was that before or after
you decided to come here?

237
00:32:23,839 --> 00:32:25,582
What are you implying?

238
00:32:27,092 --> 00:32:29,463
- Go home, Mulder.
- No, get dressed.

239
00:32:29,552 --> 00:32:32,089
- It's late.
- Get dressed.

240
00:32:32,180 --> 00:32:36,639
- What are you doing?
- Get dressed and I'll explain on the way.

241
00:34:25,938 --> 00:34:28,095
Got something to show me?

242
00:34:35,363 --> 00:34:39,940
We brought the atmosphere back down
to freezing, to control the development...

243
00:34:40,033 --> 00:34:43,068
...which is like nothing we've ever seen.

244
00:34:43,161 --> 00:34:46,280
- Brought on by what?
- Heat, I think.

245
00:34:46,371 --> 00:34:48,908
The coincident invasion of a host...

246
00:34:48,999 --> 00:34:51,204
...the fireman...

247
00:34:51,292 --> 00:34:56,914
...and an environment that raised
his body temperature above 98.6.

248
00:35:05,762 --> 00:35:07,837
This man's still alive.

249
00:35:07,931 --> 00:35:10,717
Technically... and biologically.

250
00:35:10,808 --> 00:35:13,132
But... he'll never recover.

251
00:35:17,021 --> 00:35:18,479
How can this be?

252
00:35:18,564 --> 00:35:24,683
The developing organism is using
his life energy, digesting bone and tissue.

253
00:35:25,737 --> 00:35:28,441
We've just... slowed the process.

254
00:35:31,033 --> 00:35:34,531
Shall we destroy this one, too?
Before it gestates?

255
00:35:34,619 --> 00:35:37,287
Uh, no. No.

256
00:35:37,371 --> 00:35:40,703
We need to try our vaccine on it.

257
00:35:40,790 --> 00:35:43,114
And if it's unsuccessful?

258
00:35:43,209 --> 00:35:46,624
Burn it. Like the others.

259
00:36:09,939 --> 00:36:13,354
- ID and floor you're visiting.
- The morgue.

260
00:36:14,776 --> 00:36:17,266
That area's currently off limits.

261
00:36:17,362 --> 00:36:19,686
- On whose orders?
- General McAddie.

262
00:36:19,780 --> 00:36:23,990
We were woken at 3am and told
to get down here immediately.

263
00:36:24,076 --> 00:36:26,032
I don't know about that.

264
00:36:26,119 --> 00:36:28,953
- Call General McAddie.
- I don't have the number.

265
00:36:29,038 --> 00:36:30,531
Call the switchboard.

266
00:36:33,541 --> 00:36:35,200
You don't know their number?

267
00:36:35,293 --> 00:36:40,368
- I'll call my CO.
- We don't have time for you to dick around.

268
00:36:40,464 --> 00:36:43,168
Our order came from McAddie. Call him.

269
00:36:43,258 --> 00:36:47,835
We'll conduct our business
while you confirm authorisation.

270
00:36:49,638 --> 00:36:53,504
Why don't you head on down,
and I'll confirm authorisation.

271
00:36:53,599 --> 00:36:55,306
Thank you.

272
00:36:55,393 --> 00:36:59,852
Why is the morgue suddenly off limits
on the orders of the general?

273
00:36:59,980 --> 00:37:03,727
This is one of the firemen
who died in Dallas?

274
00:37:03,816 --> 00:37:05,772
According to the toe tag.

275
00:37:05,859 --> 00:37:09,523
- And you're looking for...?
- Cause of death.

276
00:37:09,612 --> 00:37:13,229
I can tell you that
without even looking at him.

277
00:37:13,324 --> 00:37:18,565
"Concussive organ failure due to
exposure to source and flying debris."

278
00:37:18,661 --> 00:37:22,076
Mulder, this man's already been autopsied.

279
00:37:26,042 --> 00:37:29,659
Does this fit the description
you just read me?

280
00:37:34,424 --> 00:37:38,088
- Oh, my God! This man's tissue...
- It's like jelly.

281
00:37:40,679 --> 00:37:45,090
There's been some kind
of cellular breakdown.

282
00:37:49,103 --> 00:37:52,019
God, it's completely oedematous!

283
00:37:53,856 --> 00:37:58,149
There's been no autopsy performed.
No Y-incision...

284
00:37:59,027 --> 00:38:00,770
...no internal exam.

285
00:38:00,862 --> 00:38:04,526
So the cause of death on that report is false?

286
00:38:04,615 --> 00:38:07,485
This man didn't die from an explosion?

287
00:38:07,576 --> 00:38:13,161
I can't tell you what killed this man.
I'm not sure anybody else could, either.

288
00:38:19,252 --> 00:38:23,414
Mulder, you knew this man
didn't die at the bomb site.

289
00:38:23,505 --> 00:38:27,252
- I'd been told as much.
- You're saying this is a cover-up?

290
00:38:27,342 --> 00:38:28,800
Of what?

291
00:38:28,885 --> 00:38:33,462
I don't know. But I've a hunch it won't be
anything that can be categorised.

292
00:38:33,555 --> 00:38:40,267
Mulder, this is gonna take time. Somebody
is gonna figure out we shouldn't be here.

293
00:38:40,352 --> 00:38:45,593
We are being blamed for this man's death.
I want to know what he died of. Don't you?

294
00:39:01,912 --> 00:39:04,698
That's it, up here.

295
00:39:25,055 --> 00:39:29,348
- Excuse me? Can I help you?
- Is this Dr Kurtzweil's residence?

296
00:39:31,394 --> 00:39:35,770
- You have business with him?
- Yeah, I'm looking for him.

297
00:39:35,856 --> 00:39:38,013
Looking for him for what?

298
00:39:39,734 --> 00:39:44,441
The Feds are lookin' for him, too.
Nice business he's got, huh?

299
00:39:44,529 --> 00:39:46,521
What's that?

300
00:39:46,614 --> 00:39:50,776
Selling naked pictures of little kids
on his computer.

301
00:39:55,413 --> 00:39:59,279
You looking for him
for some other reason?

302
00:39:59,458 --> 00:40:03,537
Yeah. I had an appointment
for a pelvic examination.

303
00:40:10,175 --> 00:40:14,337
- You want a call ifwe find this Kurtzweil?
- Don't bother.

304
00:40:36,863 --> 00:40:40,195
See this crap?
Somebody knows I'm talking to you.

305
00:40:40,283 --> 00:40:42,607
Not according to the men in blue.

306
00:40:42,701 --> 00:40:46,199
Is it kiddie porn again?
Sexual battery of a patient?

307
00:40:46,288 --> 00:40:50,865
- They wanna discredit you. Why?
- Because I know too much about the truth.

308
00:40:50,958 --> 00:40:53,993
That end-of-the-world garbage you write?

309
00:40:54,086 --> 00:40:55,912
You know my work?

310
00:40:58,089 --> 00:41:00,544
- I was right about Dallas.
- How?

311
00:41:00,633 --> 00:41:03,205
Do you know of the Hanta virus?

312
00:41:03,301 --> 00:41:09,338
Yeah. A deadly virus spread by field mice
several years ago.

313
00:41:09,431 --> 00:41:13,842
The newspaper says FEMA was called out
to manage an outbreak.

314
00:41:13,935 --> 00:41:19,604
Do you know what the Federal Emergency
Management Agency's real power is?

315
00:41:19,690 --> 00:41:25,145
It can suspend constitutional government
upon declaration of a national emergency.

316
00:41:25,236 --> 00:41:27,275
Think about that.

317
00:41:27,363 --> 00:41:34,111
What is such a powerful agency doing
managing a small viral outbreak in Texas?

318
00:41:34,327 --> 00:41:39,996
- You saying it wasn't a small outbreak?
- No. I'm saying it wasn't the Hanta virus.

319
00:41:40,081 --> 00:41:41,824
Well, what was it?

320
00:41:47,671 --> 00:41:49,746
What was it?

321
00:41:52,008 --> 00:41:57,760
Years ago, your father and I were recruited
for a project. Biological warfare. A virus.

322
00:41:57,846 --> 00:41:59,754
What killed those men?

323
00:41:59,847 --> 00:42:04,840
Something lwon't even write about.
We have no context for what it is.

324
00:42:04,935 --> 00:42:08,978
Or any appreciation of the scale
at which it will be unleashed.

325
00:42:09,063 --> 00:42:11,138
A plague?

326
00:42:12,608 --> 00:42:14,765
The plague to end all plagues.

327
00:42:14,859 --> 00:42:17,563
A silent weapon for a quiet war.

328
00:42:17,653 --> 00:42:23,405
The systematic release of an indiscriminate
organism for which there is no cure.

329
00:42:23,491 --> 00:42:26,693
They've been working on this for 50 years.

330
00:42:26,786 --> 00:42:33,072
While the rest of the world fought Commies,
these men were negotiating an Armageddon.

331
00:42:33,166 --> 00:42:35,490
Negotiating with whom?

332
00:42:35,584 --> 00:42:37,741
I think you know.

333
00:42:37,836 --> 00:42:43,837
The timetable has been set. It'll happen
on a holiday when people are travelling.

334
00:42:43,925 --> 00:42:49,380
A state of emergency will be declared.
Government will come under the power...

335
00:42:49,471 --> 00:42:52,637
...of the Federal Emergency
Management Agency.

336
00:42:53,516 --> 00:42:57,050
FEMA. The secret government.

337
00:42:58,561 --> 00:43:00,636
They call me paranoid!

338
00:43:00,730 --> 00:43:04,347
Go back to Dallas, Agent Mulder, and dig.

339
00:43:05,359 --> 00:43:10,269
Or we'll find out along with the rest
of the country... when it's too late.

340
00:44:02,921 --> 00:44:04,712
Scully, it's me.

341
00:44:05,465 --> 00:44:08,002
- Yeah.
- Whyare you whispering?

342
00:44:08,092 --> 00:44:09,918
I can't talk right now.

343
00:44:10,010 --> 00:44:14,505
- What did you find?
- Evidence of a massive infection.

344
00:44:14,597 --> 00:44:18,095
- What kind of infection?
- I don'tknow.

345
00:44:19,434 --> 00:44:22,517
I'm gonna book a flight to Dallas.

346
00:44:22,603 --> 00:44:24,394
I'll getyou a ticket, too.

347
00:44:24,480 --> 00:44:27,017
- Mulder...
- I need your expertise.

348
00:44:27,107 --> 00:44:30,890
- It's my hearing tomorrow.
- I'll get you back in time.

349
00:44:30,985 --> 00:44:33,142
Maybe with new evidence.

350
00:44:33,237 --> 00:44:36,605
I can't!
I'm past the point of common sense here.

351
00:44:36,698 --> 00:44:40,741
It's not common sense. It's...

352
00:44:41,410 --> 00:44:44,778
Are you there? Scul...

353
00:44:44,871 --> 00:44:46,946
Scully?

354
00:45:18,899 --> 00:45:21,685
You're looking for a needle in a haystack.

355
00:45:21,776 --> 00:45:25,772
There was so much devastation,
we haven't put much together yet.

356
00:45:25,863 --> 00:45:30,274
I'm looking for anything unusual.
Maybe something from the FEMA offices...

357
00:45:30,367 --> 00:45:35,111
...where the bodies were found.
- We sent those remains off to Washington.

358
00:45:35,204 --> 00:45:38,786
Anything that you haven't sent off yet?

359
00:45:38,873 --> 00:45:45,325
Some bone fragments FEMA recovered
from an archaeological site outta town.

360
00:45:45,420 --> 00:45:48,788
- Have you examined them?
- No. They're just fossils.

361
00:45:51,759 --> 00:45:55,423
I'd like you to let this person
take a look at them.

362
00:45:58,723 --> 00:46:00,964
Just let me get them.

363
00:46:04,728 --> 00:46:08,178
- You said you weren't coming.
- I wasn't planning to.

364
00:46:08,272 --> 00:46:13,810
But I got a better look at the samples
I took from the fireman.

365
00:46:13,902 --> 00:46:15,645
And what did you find?

366
00:46:15,737 --> 00:46:20,611
Something I couldn't show to anybody else
without causing attention.

367
00:46:22,742 --> 00:46:29,277
But what those men were infected with
contains a protein coat I've never seen before.

368
00:46:29,373 --> 00:46:31,080
What it did to them, it did very fast.

369
00:46:31,166 --> 00:46:34,285
- How was it contracted?
- I don't know.

370
00:46:34,377 --> 00:46:38,623
But it could be a serious health threat.

371
00:46:40,340 --> 00:46:45,380
These fossils weren't near the blast centre
so they won't tell you much.

372
00:46:45,469 --> 00:46:48,588
Right. Why don't you check this out?

373
00:47:08,529 --> 00:47:13,486
- Where were these found?
- I'll show you right on the map.

374
00:47:48,854 --> 00:47:51,973
I want all of these settings checked.

375
00:47:52,065 --> 00:47:57,687
I want a steady minus two degrees Celsius
throughout the transfer of the body...

376
00:47:57,778 --> 00:48:00,185
...after I've administered the vaccine.

377
00:48:36,100 --> 00:48:38,139
- It's gone!
- It's what?

378
00:48:38,227 --> 00:48:41,677
It's left the body. I think it's gestated.

379
00:48:43,398 --> 00:48:46,896
- What's the matter?
- Wait.

380
00:48:48,610 --> 00:48:50,103
I can see it.

381
00:48:58,410 --> 00:48:59,654
Oh...

382
00:48:59,744 --> 00:49:02,032
Jesus, Lord...

383
00:49:04,331 --> 00:49:06,702
- You see it?
- Yeah.

384
00:49:06,792 --> 00:49:09,247
So much for little green men!

385
00:49:11,337 --> 00:49:14,787
I need you down here.

386
00:50:17,599 --> 00:50:20,089
Help... I need help.

387
00:50:26,606 --> 00:50:28,598
What are you doing?

388
00:50:30,234 --> 00:50:31,562
What are you doing!

389
00:50:39,116 --> 00:50:41,784
Oh, my God!

390
00:51:09,933 --> 00:51:12,008
Sir, you have a call.

391
00:51:24,528 --> 00:51:25,606
Yes?

392
00:51:25,696 --> 00:51:29,194
We have a situation.
The members are assembling.

393
00:51:29,282 --> 00:51:30,526
Is it an emergency?

394
00:51:30,616 --> 00:51:35,691
Yes. A meeting has been set,
tonight in London.

395
00:51:35,787 --> 00:51:37,578
Who called it?

396
00:51:37,664 --> 00:51:41,743
Strughold. He just got on a plane in Tunis.

397
00:52:13,776 --> 00:52:18,104
- Has Strughold arrived?
- Yes. They're in the library, sir.

398
00:52:29,998 --> 00:52:35,335
We were worried. Some of us have travelled
so far, and you are the last to arrive.

399
00:52:35,419 --> 00:52:38,834
I'm sorry. My grandson broke his leg.

400
00:52:38,922 --> 00:52:46,335
While we've been waiting, we've seen
surveillance tapes that raise more concerns.

401
00:52:46,428 --> 00:52:48,835
More concerns than what?

402
00:52:48,930 --> 00:52:53,140
We have been forced to reassess
our role in colonisation...

403
00:52:53,225 --> 00:52:57,767
...by recently presented facts of biology.

404
00:52:57,854 --> 00:52:59,645
The virus has mutated.

405
00:52:59,730 --> 00:53:01,769
Into what?

406
00:53:01,857 --> 00:53:05,806
A new extraterrestrial biological entity.

407
00:53:07,236 --> 00:53:09,275
My God...

408
00:53:09,363 --> 00:53:14,818
The geometry of mass infection means
we must re-evaluate their colonisation.

409
00:53:14,909 --> 00:53:20,329
This isn't colonisation.
This is spontaneous repopulation.

410
00:53:21,915 --> 00:53:23,574
All our work...

411
00:53:23,666 --> 00:53:28,825
If it's true, they've been using us all along.
We've been labouring under a lie.

412
00:53:28,920 --> 00:53:32,963
- It could be an isolated case.
- How can we know?

413
00:53:33,132 --> 00:53:37,045
We're going to tell them
what we've learned...

414
00:53:37,135 --> 00:53:41,594
...by turning over a body
infected with the gestating organism.

415
00:53:41,681 --> 00:53:45,630
In hope of what?
Learning that it's true?

416
00:53:45,726 --> 00:53:50,470
That we are nothing but digestives
for the creation of a new race of aliens?

417
00:53:50,563 --> 00:53:53,729
By co-operating
we hasten our own demise.

418
00:53:53,816 --> 00:53:57,231
It's the only chance of saving ourselves.

419
00:53:57,318 --> 00:54:00,520
They still need us to make their preparations.

420
00:54:00,613 --> 00:54:06,033
We'll continue to use them as they do us,
if only to get more time to work...

421
00:54:06,117 --> 00:54:07,908
...on our vaccine.

422
00:54:07,994 --> 00:54:14,113
My lateness might as well have been
absence. A course has already been taken.

423
00:54:14,207 --> 00:54:16,448
There are complications.

424
00:54:16,542 --> 00:54:20,870
Mulder saw one of the infected bodies
we destroyed in Dallas.

425
00:54:20,963 --> 00:54:23,583
He's there now. Someone tipped him.

426
00:54:23,673 --> 00:54:24,704
Who?

427
00:54:26,676 --> 00:54:31,716
- Kurtzweil, we think.
- No-one believes Kurtzweil. Or his books.

428
00:54:31,805 --> 00:54:33,713
He's a crank.

429
00:54:33,806 --> 00:54:35,465
Mulder believes him.

430
00:54:35,558 --> 00:54:40,384
- Then Kurtzweil must be removed.
- As must Mulder.

431
00:54:40,478 --> 00:54:46,431
Kill Mulder... we take the risk
of turning one man's quest into a crusade.

432
00:54:46,525 --> 00:54:49,809
Then take away
what he holds most valuable.

433
00:54:49,903 --> 00:54:53,235
That with which he can't live without.

434
00:54:57,367 --> 00:55:02,704
I don't see any evidence of an archaeological
or any other kind of a dig site.

435
00:55:02,788 --> 00:55:05,622
This is where he marked on the map.

436
00:55:05,707 --> 00:55:10,948
You're sure those fossils were infected
with the same virus you saw at the morgue?

437
00:55:11,045 --> 00:55:16,465
Both sets of bones were porous.
As ifthe virus were decomposing it.

438
00:55:16,549 --> 00:55:19,335
- And you've never seen that virus before?
- No.

439
00:55:22,471 --> 00:55:24,546
Look at that.

440
00:55:37,650 --> 00:55:42,357
- That look like new grass to you?
- Pretty green for this climate.

441
00:55:47,032 --> 00:55:50,779
Ground's dry about an inch down.
This was laid recently.

442
00:55:50,869 --> 00:55:52,861
The equipment's brand-new, too.

443
00:55:52,954 --> 00:55:57,081
No irrigation system.
Somebody's covering their tracks.

444
00:56:04,505 --> 00:56:05,583
Hey!

445
00:56:06,965 --> 00:56:08,043
Hey!

446
00:56:09,175 --> 00:56:11,546
You boys live around here?

447
00:56:11,636 --> 00:56:12,667
Yeah.

448
00:56:12,761 --> 00:56:15,002
Seen anybody digging over there?

449
00:56:15,097 --> 00:56:17,385
We're not supposed to say.

450
00:56:17,474 --> 00:56:20,390
- Who told you that?
- Nobody.

451
00:56:20,476 --> 00:56:23,760
Same nobody that built that playground?

452
00:56:23,854 --> 00:56:27,850
Nobody buy you those new bikes, too?

453
00:56:27,940 --> 00:56:31,272
- You'd better tell us.
- We don't even know you.

454
00:56:31,360 --> 00:56:32,853
We're FBI agents.

455
00:56:32,944 --> 00:56:34,687
You're not FBI agents.

456
00:56:34,779 --> 00:56:39,238
- How do you know?
- Cos y'all look like door-to-door salesmen.

457
00:56:43,286 --> 00:56:45,574
Hey, you wanna buy a badge?

458
00:56:46,664 --> 00:56:48,620
They left an hour ago.

459
00:56:48,707 --> 00:56:50,829
Going that way.

460
00:57:04,011 --> 00:57:06,501
Unmarked tanker trucks.

461
00:57:06,597 --> 00:57:09,881
What do archaeologists
haul out in tanker trucks?

462
00:57:09,974 --> 00:57:12,760
- I don't know.
- Where are they going with it?

463
00:57:12,852 --> 00:57:16,516
That's the first question to answer
if we're gonna find them.

464
00:57:26,279 --> 00:57:27,772
What are my choices?

465
00:57:27,947 --> 00:57:32,524
- 100 miles of nothing in both directions.
- Which way do you think they went?

466
00:57:32,659 --> 00:57:34,900
You got two choices. One's wrong.

467
00:57:38,914 --> 00:57:41,949
- I think they went left.
- I think they went right.

468
00:57:59,806 --> 00:58:04,099
Five years together.
How many times have I been wrong?

469
00:58:04,185 --> 00:58:06,260
Never.

470
00:58:06,937 --> 00:58:08,680
Not driving, anyway.

471
00:58:54,351 --> 00:58:58,050
- I was right about the bomb, wasn't I?
- This is great. This is fitting.

472
00:58:58,145 --> 00:59:00,635
What?

473
00:59:00,731 --> 00:59:07,811
I have to be in Washington DC in 11 hours
for a hearing concerning my career.

474
00:59:07,903 --> 00:59:12,860
And I'm in the middle of nowhere,
chasing phantom tanker trucks.

475
00:59:12,949 --> 00:59:15,024
We're chasing evidence.

476
00:59:15,117 --> 00:59:16,314
Of what?

477
00:59:16,410 --> 00:59:21,450
That bomb went off to hide something:
Bodies infected with a virus you detected.

478
00:59:21,539 --> 00:59:26,959
They haul oil in tanker trucks. They haul gas
in tanker trucks. They do not haul viruses.

479
00:59:27,044 --> 00:59:30,957
Well, they may be hauling a virus
in these tanker trucks.

480
00:59:31,047 --> 00:59:33,122
What do you mean? Mulder?

481
00:59:33,215 --> 00:59:35,622
What are you not telling me?

482
00:59:36,927 --> 00:59:39,251
Mulder!

483
00:59:41,180 --> 00:59:43,717
The virus may be extraterrestrial.

484
00:59:47,936 --> 00:59:50,343
I don't...

485
00:59:50,438 --> 00:59:52,975
Mulder, I don't...

486
01:01:20,427 --> 01:01:24,174
- What do you think they are?
- I have no idea.

487
01:02:06,548 --> 01:02:08,207
This is weird, Mulder.

488
01:02:08,883 --> 01:02:10,258
Very weird.

489
01:02:10,342 --> 01:02:14,291
Why would anyone grow corn
in the middle of the desert?

490
01:02:14,387 --> 01:02:17,802
Those could be giant Jiffy Pop poppers.

491
01:03:28,823 --> 01:03:31,194
It's cool in here.

492
01:03:31,450 --> 01:03:34,284
The temperature's being regulated.

493
01:03:34,369 --> 01:03:36,444
For the purpose of what?

494
01:03:36,537 --> 01:03:41,530
I think we're on top of a larger structure.
This is some kind of a venting system.

495
01:03:41,625 --> 01:03:43,664
Do you hear something?

496
01:03:49,631 --> 01:03:52,750
I hear a humming. Like electricity.

497
01:03:54,051 --> 01:03:55,461
High voltage, maybe.

498
01:03:55,553 --> 01:03:57,461
Maybe.

499
01:04:03,059 --> 01:04:05,134
Maybe not.

500
01:04:12,566 --> 01:04:14,059
Scully...

501
01:04:14,151 --> 01:04:16,723
- Yeah?
- Run!

502
01:04:30,789 --> 01:04:31,654
Scully!

503
01:04:31,749 --> 01:04:34,286
I can't see!

504
01:04:36,836 --> 01:04:39,077
Give me your hand!

505
01:04:48,429 --> 01:04:52,212
- Did you get stung?
- I don't think so.

506
01:06:06,700 --> 01:06:08,028
Talk to me, Scully!

507
01:06:08,118 --> 01:06:10,690
Scully!

508
01:06:11,746 --> 01:06:13,453
Damn it! Scully!

509
01:06:20,045 --> 01:06:21,622
Scully!

510
01:06:22,338 --> 01:06:23,452
Scully!

511
01:06:24,423 --> 01:06:26,082
Talk to me, Scully!

512
01:06:26,174 --> 01:06:27,549
Mulder!

513
01:06:31,929 --> 01:06:33,091
Scully!

514
01:06:33,972 --> 01:06:35,549
Mulder!

515
01:06:35,640 --> 01:06:37,217
Can you hear me?

516
01:06:37,309 --> 01:06:38,008
Mulder...

517
01:06:50,402 --> 01:06:52,275
Scully!

518
01:06:55,865 --> 01:06:57,109
Scully!

519
01:06:57,533 --> 01:06:58,398
Scully!

520
01:06:59,868 --> 01:07:00,863
Mulder!

521
01:07:00,953 --> 01:07:01,948
Scully!

522
01:07:02,037 --> 01:07:03,863
Scully, talk to me!

523
01:07:03,955 --> 01:07:05,199
Mulder...

524
01:07:11,670 --> 01:07:12,867
Where'd they go?

525
01:07:16,549 --> 01:07:18,624
Come on!

526
01:07:45,155 --> 01:07:46,435
She's coming in.

527
01:07:55,330 --> 01:07:57,073
Special Agent Scully.

528
01:07:57,165 --> 01:07:59,370
I apologise for making you wait.

529
01:07:59,458 --> 01:08:01,865
I have new evidence.

530
01:08:01,960 --> 01:08:03,584
Evidence of what?

531
01:08:05,838 --> 01:08:09,372
These are fossilised bone fragments...

532
01:08:09,800 --> 01:08:14,342
...that were gathered
at the bomb site in Dallas.

533
01:08:14,429 --> 01:08:17,713
- You've been back to Dallas?
- Yes.

534
01:08:27,564 --> 01:08:31,098
- You found something.
- In Texas, some kind of experiment.

535
01:08:31,192 --> 01:08:33,647
Tankers carrying something they excavated.

536
01:08:33,736 --> 01:08:38,195
- What?
- I'm not sure. A virus, I think.

537
01:08:38,281 --> 01:08:44,614
I also have reason to believe that there may
have been involvement by SAC Michaud.

538
01:08:44,703 --> 01:08:49,410
Those are very serious allegations,
Agent Scully.

539
01:08:49,499 --> 01:08:51,823
Yes, I know.

540
01:08:51,917 --> 01:08:54,917
- You saw this experiment?
- Yeah. We were chased off.

541
01:08:55,003 --> 01:08:59,046
- What did it look like?
- There were bees, corn crops.

542
01:09:00,633 --> 01:09:04,546
And you have conclusive evidence
to tie your claim to the crime?

543
01:09:05,929 --> 01:09:14,101
Not completely conclusive. We're working
towards gathering that evidence.

544
01:09:14,185 --> 01:09:15,643
Working with?

545
01:09:18,522 --> 01:09:20,015
With Agent Mulder.

546
01:09:20,107 --> 01:09:24,103
- What are they?
- What do you think?

547
01:09:24,194 --> 01:09:29,567
Transportation system. Transgenic crops.
The pollen altered to carry a virus.

548
01:09:29,656 --> 01:09:31,031
That's my guess.

549
01:09:33,951 --> 01:09:34,864
Guess?

550
01:09:34,994 --> 01:09:38,693
What do you mean?
Hey! You told me you had answers.

551
01:09:38,789 --> 01:09:41,113
Yeah, but I don't have 'em all.

552
01:09:41,207 --> 01:09:45,286
- You didn't know my father.
- He and I were old friends.

553
01:09:45,377 --> 01:09:49,160
You've used me
to gather information for your books!

554
01:09:49,256 --> 01:09:51,212
Lower your voice!

555
01:09:54,677 --> 01:09:56,384
Kurtzweil!

556
01:09:56,470 --> 01:10:02,838
You'd be shit out of luck if it wasn't for me.
I put my ass on the line for you.

557
01:10:02,933 --> 01:10:06,265
I just got chased
by two black helicopters!

558
01:10:06,353 --> 01:10:09,803
And why do you think
you're here talking to me?

559
01:10:09,897 --> 01:10:12,185
These people don't make mistakes.

560
01:11:08,611 --> 01:11:10,686
What's wrong?

561
01:11:12,073 --> 01:11:16,022
Salt Lake City, Utah.
Transfer effective immediately.

562
01:11:16,117 --> 01:11:20,410
I already gave Skinner
my letter of resignation.

563
01:11:20,496 --> 01:11:22,404
You can't quit now.

564
01:11:22,498 --> 01:11:27,372
I can, Mulder. I debated
whether to tell you in person...

565
01:11:27,543 --> 01:11:29,914
We're on the verge here!

566
01:11:30,004 --> 01:11:33,870
You're on the verge.
Please don't do this to me.

567
01:11:33,965 --> 01:11:37,878
After all you've seen,
you can just walk away?

568
01:11:37,968 --> 01:11:40,505
I have. I did. It's done.

569
01:11:40,596 --> 01:11:44,260
- I need you on this...
- You don't need me.

570
01:11:44,641 --> 01:11:47,724
You never have.
I've just held you back.

571
01:11:52,063 --> 01:11:54,138
I gotta go.

572
01:11:57,776 --> 01:12:02,602
If you wanna tell yourselfthat, you can.
But you're wrong.

573
01:12:02,697 --> 01:12:05,187
Why did they assign me to you?

574
01:12:05,324 --> 01:12:08,110
To debunk your work.
To shut you down.

575
01:12:08,201 --> 01:12:09,908
But you saved me!

576
01:12:09,994 --> 01:12:13,741
As frustrating as it's been sometimes...

577
01:12:13,831 --> 01:12:18,871
...your strict rationalism and science
have saved me a thousand times over.

578
01:12:18,960 --> 01:12:21,035
You kept me honest.

579
01:12:22,213 --> 01:12:27,288
You made me a whole person.
I owe you everything.

580
01:12:28,634 --> 01:12:31,338
Scully, you owe me nothing.

581
01:12:35,974 --> 01:12:39,093
I don't know if I wanna do this alone.

582
01:12:41,770 --> 01:12:43,845
I don't even know if I can.

583
01:12:47,275 --> 01:12:49,730
And if I quit now, they win.

584
01:13:46,906 --> 01:13:48,364
Ow! Jesus!

585
01:13:48,449 --> 01:13:49,397
I'm sorry.

586
01:13:49,492 --> 01:13:51,982
No... Something stung me.

587
01:13:57,915 --> 01:14:00,487
Must've gotten in your shirt.

588
01:14:01,293 --> 01:14:02,371
Mulder...

589
01:14:04,045 --> 01:14:05,669
...something's wrong.

590
01:14:06,005 --> 01:14:07,202
What?

591
01:14:07,298 --> 01:14:12,671
- I'm having lancinating pain in my chest.
- What?

592
01:14:13,219 --> 01:14:14,381
Scully!

593
01:14:14,470 --> 01:14:21,005
My motor functions are being affected.
My... pulse is thready.

594
01:14:21,142 --> 01:14:25,470
I have a funny taste in the back of my throat.

595
01:14:25,562 --> 01:14:29,428
- It must be anaphylactic shock.
- I have no allergy...

596
01:14:37,739 --> 01:14:41,735
This is Special Agent Fox Mulder.
I have an agent down!

597
01:14:42,535 --> 01:14:45,784
Can you hear me?
Can you say your name?

598
01:14:45,871 --> 01:14:52,204
She has constriction in the throat.
Let's get her in the van right away!

599
01:14:53,043 --> 01:14:57,787
She said she had a funny taste in her throat.
But she has no allergy to bee stings.

600
01:14:57,880 --> 01:15:00,631
The bee that stung her
might have been carrying a virus.

601
01:15:00,716 --> 01:15:05,542
- Get on the radio. Tell them...
- Tell them it may have been carrying a virus!

602
01:15:05,637 --> 01:15:08,590
I wanna go with her.
What hospital? I...

603
01:15:09,306 --> 01:15:11,463
What hospital are you taking her to?

604
01:16:57,894 --> 01:17:00,645
- What are you doing?
- Reading his chart.

605
01:17:00,730 --> 01:17:03,350
- Put it down.
- When I'm ready.

606
01:17:03,440 --> 01:17:06,890
- I think he's coming out of it.
- He's coming to.

607
01:17:08,486 --> 01:17:10,193
Hey, Mulder.

608
01:17:10,279 --> 01:17:11,856
Mulder?

609
01:17:13,990 --> 01:17:15,649
Oh, my God...

610
01:17:18,035 --> 01:17:22,328
Cowardly Lion, Scarecrow, Toto.

611
01:17:26,209 --> 01:17:28,248
What am I doin' here?

612
01:17:28,335 --> 01:17:32,794
- A bullet grazed your temporal plate.
- 3cms left and we'd be playing harps.

613
01:17:32,881 --> 01:17:35,453
You've been unconscious since you got here.

614
01:17:35,925 --> 01:17:37,087
Where's Scully?

615
01:17:37,176 --> 01:17:40,710
Your 911 call must have been intercepted.

616
01:17:40,971 --> 01:17:45,347
Scully had a reaction
to a honeybee we found in your hall.

617
01:17:45,433 --> 01:17:49,132
- I gotta get to her.
- You're staying right here.

618
01:17:49,227 --> 01:17:51,266
This goes back to Dallas.

619
01:17:51,354 --> 01:17:55,018
- Where is she? I'll find her.
- I don't know where she is.

620
01:17:55,107 --> 01:18:01,108
You leave here unprotected, how far
will you get? How far will they let you get?

621
01:18:01,195 --> 01:18:03,317
What can we do?

622
01:18:05,365 --> 01:18:07,238
You can strip Byers naked.

623
01:18:07,325 --> 01:18:08,522
What?

624
01:18:08,618 --> 01:18:11,322
I need your clothes.

625
01:18:40,435 --> 01:18:42,510
It's Mulder.

626
01:19:16,506 --> 01:19:19,376
Dr Kurtzweil? Dr Alvin Kurtzweil.

627
01:20:11,592 --> 01:20:13,002
Mr Mulder.

628
01:20:15,554 --> 01:20:18,091
What happened to Kurtzweil?

629
01:20:18,181 --> 01:20:21,015
He's come and gone.

630
01:20:21,100 --> 01:20:22,843
Where's Scully?

631
01:20:22,935 --> 01:20:28,010
The location of Agent Scully
and the means to save her life.

632
01:20:28,106 --> 01:20:29,765
Please.

633
01:21:09,431 --> 01:21:11,138
What is it?

634
01:21:11,224 --> 01:21:15,267
A weak vaccine against the virus
she's been infected with.

635
01:21:15,352 --> 01:21:18,305
It must be administered within 96 hours.

636
01:21:18,397 --> 01:21:21,350
That leaves you little time to get there.

637
01:21:23,818 --> 01:21:28,562
- You're lying.
- No. Though I can't prove it.

638
01:21:28,738 --> 01:21:32,437
The virus is extraterrestrial.
We know little about it...

639
01:21:32,533 --> 01:21:35,948
...except that it was
the original inhabitant of Earth.

640
01:21:37,662 --> 01:21:39,286
- A virus?
- What is a virus...

641
01:21:39,372 --> 01:21:43,534
...but a colonising force
that cannot be defeated?

642
01:21:43,625 --> 01:21:48,582
Living in a cave, underground,
until it mutates and attacks.

643
01:21:49,088 --> 01:21:52,420
This is what you've been
conspiring to conceal?

644
01:21:52,507 --> 01:21:56,373
- A disease?
- No, you've got it all backwards.

645
01:21:56,469 --> 01:22:01,842
AIDS, the Ebola virus,
on an evolutionary scale, they're newborns.

646
01:22:01,932 --> 01:22:06,059
This virus walked the planet
long before the dinosaurs.

647
01:22:06,144 --> 01:22:07,175
Walked?

648
01:22:07,269 --> 01:22:13,934
Your aliens, your little green men,
arrived here millions of years ago.

649
01:22:14,025 --> 01:22:18,068
Those that didn't leave
have been lying dormant...

650
01:22:18,153 --> 01:22:21,437
...in the form of an evolved pathogen...

651
01:22:21,531 --> 01:22:28,742
...waiting to be reconstituted by the alien race
when it comes to colonise the planet...

652
01:22:28,829 --> 01:22:30,536
...using us as hosts.

653
01:22:30,622 --> 01:22:34,998
Against this, we have no defence.
Nothing but a weak vaccine.

654
01:22:35,084 --> 01:22:37,870
Do you see why it was kept secret?

655
01:22:38,044 --> 01:22:43,250
Why even men like your father
could not let the truth be known?

656
01:22:43,340 --> 01:22:49,258
Until Dallas, we believed the virus would
simply control us. Make us a slave race.

657
01:22:52,306 --> 01:22:57,346
Imagine our surprise
when they began to gestate.

658
01:22:57,477 --> 01:23:01,260
My group has been working
with the alien colonists...

659
01:23:01,355 --> 01:23:06,016
...facilitating programmes
to give us access to the virus...

660
01:23:06,109 --> 01:23:08,681
...in the hope of developing a cure.

661
01:23:10,446 --> 01:23:12,105
To save your own asses.

662
01:23:12,197 --> 01:23:16,941
Survival is the ultimate ideology.
Your father wisely refused to believe this.

663
01:23:17,034 --> 01:23:20,236
But he sacrificed my sister.

664
01:23:20,329 --> 01:23:26,662
With no vaccine, the only true survivors of
the viral holocaust will be those immune to it.

665
01:23:26,750 --> 01:23:33,629
Human alien clones. He allowed your sister
to be abducted, for one reason.

666
01:23:36,633 --> 01:23:38,708
So she would survive.

667
01:23:40,470 --> 01:23:42,296
As a genetic hybrid.

668
01:23:42,388 --> 01:23:46,005
Your father chose hope over selfishness.

669
01:23:46,224 --> 01:23:50,055
Hope in the only future he had, his children.

670
01:23:50,144 --> 01:23:53,179
He hoped youwould uncover the truth.

671
01:23:53,272 --> 01:23:56,971
That you would stop the project,
that you would fight the future.

672
01:24:03,280 --> 01:24:07,656
- Why are you telling me this?
- For the sake of my own children.

673
01:24:07,742 --> 01:24:12,201
Once it's learned what I've told you,
my life will be over.

674
01:24:20,085 --> 01:24:22,124
Where's Dr Kurtzweil?

675
01:24:26,340 --> 01:24:28,830
I'd like to get out of the car now.

676
01:24:30,385 --> 01:24:31,380
Stop the car!

677
01:24:33,471 --> 01:24:35,048
Driver...

678
01:24:55,822 --> 01:25:01,906
The men I work with will strongly protect
their stake in the inevitable future.

679
01:25:03,454 --> 01:25:09,039
I was ordered to kill Dr Kurtzweil.
As I was ordered to kill you.

680
01:25:14,588 --> 01:25:16,165
Trust no-one, Mr Mulder.

681
01:25:20,884 --> 01:25:22,342
Get out of the car.

682
01:25:25,221 --> 01:25:27,889
Why? The upholstery's already ruined.

683
01:25:27,974 --> 01:25:29,633
Get out of the car!

684
01:25:39,983 --> 01:25:42,473
You have precious little time.

685
01:25:42,569 --> 01:25:48,191
What I've given you,
the alien colonists don't yet know exists.

686
01:25:48,282 --> 01:25:51,732
That vaccine is the only defence
against the virus.

687
01:25:51,826 --> 01:25:54,945
Introducing it into an alien environment...

688
01:25:55,037 --> 01:26:00,741
...may destroy the plans we have so
assiduously protected for the last 50 years.

689
01:26:00,833 --> 01:26:03,288
What do you mean, may?

690
01:26:03,377 --> 01:26:09,248
Find Agent Scully. Only then
will you realise the scope of the project.

691
01:26:10,466 --> 01:26:11,247
Go!

692
01:26:13,052 --> 01:26:15,127
Go now!

693
01:34:50,512 --> 01:34:51,543
Shit!

694
01:37:15,004 --> 01:37:18,835
Secure the station!
I want everyone else below.

695
01:37:18,924 --> 01:37:21,794
Arm yourselves.
We may have a breach.

696
01:37:36,772 --> 01:37:38,598
Let's go! Let's go!

697
01:38:20,432 --> 01:38:21,594
Scully?

698
01:38:36,028 --> 01:38:38,600
There's a contaminant in the system.

699
01:38:40,657 --> 01:38:43,147
Mulder has the vaccine.

700
01:39:03,425 --> 01:39:05,216
Breathe!

701
01:39:05,302 --> 01:39:06,961
Scully, can you breathe?

702
01:39:14,392 --> 01:39:15,933
Cold...

703
01:39:16,019 --> 01:39:18,687
- I'm cold...
- I'll get you out.

704
01:39:23,900 --> 01:39:27,315
Abandon your posts! Evacuate!

705
01:39:36,202 --> 01:39:39,784
- What's happened?
- It's all going to hell!

706
01:39:39,871 --> 01:39:41,910
- What about Mulder?
- He won't make it.

707
01:41:25,749 --> 01:41:27,824
We gotta keep movin'.

708
01:41:28,126 --> 01:41:29,121
Come on!

709
01:41:29,210 --> 01:41:31,700
I can't.

710
01:41:31,795 --> 01:41:33,870
Yeah, you can.

711
01:41:51,645 --> 01:41:54,479
Scully, grab that vent.

712
01:41:56,940 --> 01:41:59,644
Scully, grab the vent!

713
01:42:00,902 --> 01:42:03,226
Scully...

714
01:42:29,967 --> 01:42:31,081
Jeez, breathe!

715
01:42:37,598 --> 01:42:40,088
Breathe! Come on!

716
01:42:45,188 --> 01:42:47,263
Breathe in.

717
01:42:47,565 --> 01:42:50,399
Breathe in... Breathe!

718
01:42:51,902 --> 01:42:54,273
I had you big time.

719
01:43:10,500 --> 01:43:11,875
Pull!

720
01:43:11,960 --> 01:43:14,367
Come on, Scully! Pull!

721
01:43:17,172 --> 01:43:19,247
Mulder...

722
01:43:28,473 --> 01:43:29,883
Keep movin'!

723
01:43:35,604 --> 01:43:37,512
Go! Come on!

724
01:43:43,151 --> 01:43:45,606
Almost there. Keep going.

725
01:46:15,608 --> 01:46:17,647
You gotta see this.

726
01:46:17,735 --> 01:46:19,774
Scully!

727
01:48:00,318 --> 01:48:07,232
In light of your report and narrative,
my official report is incomplete...

728
01:48:07,324 --> 01:48:10,490
...pending these new facts
I'm being asked to reconcile.

729
01:48:10,576 --> 01:48:16,778
Though it seems that a federal agent
may have been involved in the bombing...

730
01:48:16,873 --> 01:48:21,580
...the other events you've laid down
are too incredible on their own...

731
01:48:21,669 --> 01:48:26,495
...and, quite frankly, implausible.
- What is it you find incredible?

732
01:48:26,589 --> 01:48:28,332
Where should I start?

733
01:48:28,424 --> 01:48:33,583
So many of the events
described in your report defy belief.

734
01:48:33,678 --> 01:48:36,797
Antarctica is a longway from Dallas.

735
01:48:36,889 --> 01:48:42,641
I can't give the Attorney General a report
that alleges the links you've made here.

736
01:48:42,727 --> 01:48:48,182
Bees and corn crops
don't come under domestic terrorism.

737
01:48:48,815 --> 01:48:50,972
No, they don't.

738
01:48:52,110 --> 01:48:59,321
Your report doesn't show
any organisation with an attributable motive.

739
01:48:59,658 --> 01:49:04,733
I realise your ordeal affected you,
but the holes in your account...

740
01:49:04,828 --> 01:49:09,619
...leave us with no choice
but to delete these references...

741
01:49:09,707 --> 01:49:17,416
...until hard evidence becomes available that
could cause us to pursue an investigation.

742
01:49:39,273 --> 01:49:46,816
I don't believe the FBI has an investigative
unit qualified to pursue the evidence in hand.

743
01:50:27,520 --> 01:50:31,848
There's an interesting work offiction
on page 24.

744
01:50:31,941 --> 01:50:35,190
Mysteriously,
our names have been omitted.

745
01:50:35,944 --> 01:50:41,185
They're burying it. They're gonna
dig a new hole and cover it up.

746
01:50:41,281 --> 01:50:44,447
I told OPR everything I know.

747
01:50:44,534 --> 01:50:51,199
What I experienced, the virus, how it's spread
by the bees and transgenic crops.

748
01:50:51,290 --> 01:50:52,949
They won't believe you.

749
01:50:53,041 --> 01:50:57,037
Not unless your story can be categorised
or easily referenced.

750
01:50:57,128 --> 01:50:59,452
- We'll go over their heads.
- No. No.

751
01:50:59,546 --> 01:51:02,416
How many times
have we been here before?

752
01:51:02,507 --> 01:51:05,423
Right here?
So close to the truth.

753
01:51:05,509 --> 01:51:08,959
And now,
to be back at the beginning with nothing!

754
01:51:09,054 --> 01:51:10,927
This is different.

755
01:51:11,014 --> 01:51:17,514
No, it isn't. You're right to want to quit. You
should get as far away from me as you can.

756
01:51:17,603 --> 01:51:20,935
You won't die
because of a hollow cause of mine!

757
01:51:21,022 --> 01:51:23,808
Go be a doctor.

758
01:51:23,899 --> 01:51:26,733
Go be a doctor while you still can.

759
01:51:29,779 --> 01:51:32,020
I can't. I won't.

760
01:51:32,114 --> 01:51:36,821
I'll be a doctor,
but my work is here with you now.

761
01:51:36,910 --> 01:51:39,744
That virus that I was exposed to...

762
01:51:39,829 --> 01:51:45,782
...whatever it is, it has a cure.
You held it in your hand.

763
01:51:48,461 --> 01:51:51,247
How many other lives can we save?

764
01:51:54,299 --> 01:51:56,125
Look...

765
01:52:00,429 --> 01:52:04,011
...if I quit now, they win.

766
01:52:58,351 --> 01:53:02,098
You look hot.
Why have you travelled all this way?

767
01:53:02,187 --> 01:53:04,143
We have business to discuss.

768
01:53:04,231 --> 01:53:08,808
- You have regular channels.
- This involves Mulder.

769
01:53:09,151 --> 01:53:13,479
- That name! Again and again.
- He's seen more than he should.

770
01:53:13,571 --> 01:53:17,235
Of the whole, he has seen but pieces.

771
01:53:17,324 --> 01:53:21,367
He's determined now. Reinvested.

772
01:53:24,956 --> 01:53:27,031
He's but one man.

773
01:53:27,708 --> 01:53:30,874
One man alone cannot fight the future.

774
01:53:31,544 --> 01:53:33,619
Yesterday...

775
01:53:33,880 --> 01:53:35,955
...I received this.

776
01:54:58,865 --> 01:55:01,984
Visiontext subtitles: Susan Voas

